x4freetext: Reactor spectrum. All nuclides irradiated in position
S-2 with a Cd ratio of 3.8 and in either position E-1
depending on whether products were long or short-lived
Epithermal-to-thermal flux ratio was measured in
each irradiation by including a uranium-scandium
Element scandium was used as an internal flux monitor
scandium values were measured by taking mixtures of
All counting was done on gamma spectral analyzers
to measure absolute photon emission rates.
All spectra generated were analyzed by computer code
GAMANAL to obtain a set of absolute disintegration
The disintegration-rate data thus obtained were further
analyzed by another computer code NADAC to compute the
effective cross section for each activation product.
